I noticed last night as I accidentally pulled 2 seafurbies instead of 1, and my pet was sic'd on the first mob, the second started pounding on my pet as well...  <br>
I don't dare go 'sit' at a time like that, since the second mob comes my way and I'm as good as dead.  <br>
However, as they were both pounding on my pet, I saw Jobaber change/switch targets all by itself (like it wanted to keep the two mobs close to him).  <br>
I guess that the pet itself switched attacks to the one causing it the most damage or the most taunting of the two - which was way ok in my opinion as it was my earth pet, it kept both the mobs rooted and all I had to do was nuke the first one, heal pet, nuke the first one, heal pet, see the first one die, then sit and have pet bash the second to a pulp.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, wether or not the way pets behave has changed over the years EQ has worked, this was just the best scenario any mage can have when dealing with 2 mobs at the same time without having intended it.<br>
<br>
Just my two cents - my pet obeys me quite well with regards to aggro lists and such, but it also seems to notice when to divert it's attention to another mob when you have 2 mobs on you (or it)...<br>
<br>
